PAGE.DESCRIPTION:
We can take powers of square matrices by doing matrix multiplication.  We thus have:
\begin{equation}
 \left(
 \begin{matrix}
  a & b \\
  c & d
 \end{matrix}
\right)^2 = 
\left(
 \begin{matrix}
  a & b \\
  c & d
 \end{matrix}
\right)
\left(
 \begin{matrix}
  a & b \\
  c & d
 \end{matrix}
\right) = 
\left(
 \begin{matrix}
  a^2 + bc & ab + bd \\
  ca + dc & bc + d^2
 \end{matrix}
\right)
\end{equation}
